# API

Python 3.12 FastAPI application. Core data store and query engine.

**Entry point:** `api/main.py` · **Port:** 8080

## Data Model

| Entity | ID Format | Description |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| **Data** | `data_<ULID>` | Any stored content — text, files, URLs. Versioned. |
| **Memory** | `mem_<type>_<ULID>` | Container grouping data items. 10 types. |
| **User** | UUID | User identity with username, email, roles. |
| **Embedding** | UUID | Vector embedding chunk (pgvector). |
| **Viewpoint** | UUID | AI-generated analysis of a data item. Versioned. |
| **Prompt** | UUID | Reusable prompt template. |
| **Skill** | UUID | AI agent role definition. |

### Memory types

| Type | Duration | Purpose |
|------|----------|---------|
| `timeline` | permanent | Chronological activity log |
| `session` | temporary | Bounded interaction session |
| `conversation` | temporary | Multi-turn dialogue |
| `user` | permanent | User profile facts |
| `organizational` | permanent | Org-level knowledge |
| `factual` | permanent | Verified facts |
| `episodic` | temporary | Event memories |
| `semantic` | permanent | Conceptual knowledge |
| `custom` | varies | User-defined |
| `tracing` | temporary | OTel trace spans |

| **Organization** | `org_<ULID>` | Team or company container. |
| **Project** | `proj_<ULID>` | App-level scope within an org. |

### Storage tables (Supabase)

- **`mem_dog_blobs`** — General blob store keyed by `(store_name, path)`, with optional `user_id`, `org_id`, `project_id` scoping
- **`mem_dog_embeddings`** — pgvector embeddings with `data_id`, `chunk_text`, `vector`, `ai_signature`, optional `org_id`/`project_id`
- **`organizations`** — Org hierarchy: `org_id`, `name`, `owner_user_id`, `status`
- **`projects`** — Projects within orgs: `project_id`, `org_id` (FK), `name`, `status`
- **`org_members`** — Membership: `(org_id, user_id)` composite PK, `role` (owner/admin/member/viewer)
- **`mem_dog_entities`** — Knowledge graph entities with `entity_type`, `canonical_form`, dedup index
- **`mem_dog_relationships`** — Directed relationships between entities
- **`mem_dog_entity_data_mapping`** — Entity-to-data-item links
- **`agent_configs`** — Per-agent-type pipeline configs scoped by `(agent_type, user_id)`. `NULL` user_id = system default.

## Authentication

Dual-path auth via `X-API-Key` header:

| Auth type | Key format | Scope |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Global | Any string (set via `API_KEY` env) | Full access, no user scope |
| Per-user | `md_<token>` (44 chars) | Scoped to `user_id` |

Public paths (`/`, `/health`, `/docs`, `/redoc`, `/openapi.json`) never require a key. If `API_KEY` env is unset (local dev), all requests pass through.

Per-user keys are managed via `POST /api/v1/users/{id}/api-keys` (returned once), listed via `GET`, and revoked via `DELETE`.

## Endpoints

### Health & Info

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/` | Service info |
| GET | `/health` | Health probe |

### Data (`/api/v1/data`)

CRUD for data items: create (file upload, URL, inline), list, get (raw content or metadata), update (creates new version), delete. Per-item access control via `/data/{id}/access`.

### Tags (`/api/v1`)

Tag operations on data items: get, replace, add, remove. Global: list all tags, search by tags (ANY/ALL mode).

### Versions (`/api/v1/versions`)

List version history and retrieve content at specific versions.

### Memories (`/api/v1/memories`)

CRUD for memory containers. Associate/disassociate data items. Bulk delete.

**Mem0 Categories** — 10 granular types grouped into 4 Mem0-aligned categories:

| Memory Type | Category | Default TTL |
|------------|----------|-------------|
| conversation | conversation | 1 hour |
| timeline | session | 7 days |
| session | session | 24 hours |
| tracing | session | 3 days |
| user, factual, episodic, semantic, custom | user | never |
| organizational | organizational | never |

**Access Levels** — `private` (default), `shared`, `public`, `restricted`. Use `shared_with` to specify user IDs for shared/restricted access.

**Expiry** — All types support `ttl_hours` and `no_expiry`. Expired memories are hidden by default; use `include_expired=true` to include them.

**New Query Params** (GET `/api/v1/memories`):
- `access_level` — Filter by access level
- `category` — Filter by Mem0 category
- `include_expired` — Include expired memories (default false)

**New Create Fields** (`POST /api/v1/memories`):
- `access_level` — Access level (default: private)
- `shared_with` — List of user IDs
- `no_expiry` — Override default TTL (boolean)

**New Update Fields** (`PUT /api/v1/memories/{id}`):
- `access_level`, `shared_with`, `expires_at` — Update access/expiry directly

### Organizations & Projects (`/api/v1/organizations`, `/api/v1/projects`)

Org/project hierarchy for multi-tenant scoping. See [Organizations](organizations.md) for full details.

- **Orgs**: CRUD + membership management (owner/admin/member/viewer roles)
- **Projects**: CRUD nested under orgs
- **Scoping**: Pass `?project_id=proj_...` on data, memories, and embeddings endpoints to scope queries

### Users (`/api/v1/users`)

User CRUD, per-user data upload/listing, username lookup, API key management.

### AI Config (`/api/v1/ai`)

System AI config, model catalog, pipeline models, agent processing defaults, per-user engine configs and preferences, Ollama Cloud model cards, smart routing config and suggestions.

### AI Query (`/api/v1/ai/query`)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/ai/query` | Natural language query (RAG) |
| POST | `/ai/query/timeline` | Timeline-scoped RAG |
| POST | `/ai/query/semantic` | Vector similarity search |
| POST | `/ai/query/chat` | Conversational RAG with inline citations |

### AI Resources

Prompts, Embeddings, Viewpoints, Skills, Agent Configs, Analysis Templates — all CRUD.

### Graph Memory (`/api/v1/graph`)

Entity/relationship knowledge graph. Entities are auto-extracted by the webhook pipeline.

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/graph/entities?q=&user_id=` | Search entities by name |
| GET | `/graph/entities/{id}` | Entity detail |
| GET | `/graph/entities/{id}/relationships` | Entity relationships |
| GET | `/graph/data/{data_id}/entities` | Entities in a data item |
| POST | `/graph/entities/batch` | Batch create entities + relationships |
| DELETE | `/graph/entities/{id}` | Delete entity (cascades) |
| DELETE | `/graph/data/{data_id}/entities` | Delete all entities for data item |

Entity types: `person`, `organization`, `product`, `location`, `date`, `url`, `concept`, `event`.

See [Graph Memory](graph-memory.md) for schema details.

### Memory Compression (`/api/v1/memories/{id}/compress`)

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/memories/{id}/compress` | LLM-summarize memory into compressed data item |

Request body: `{"archive_originals": false, "max_summary_length": 2000}`

Auto-compression triggers when a memory exceeds `AUTO_COMPRESS_THRESHOLD` items (default 50, env-configurable).

### Other

- **Statistics** (`/stats`) — Global/per-user stats, token usage tracking
- **Channels & Identities** — Channel→user bindings, channel config
- **Ingest** (`/ingest`) — Universal envelope ingestion (`direct=true` stores, `direct=false` forwards to pipeline)
- **Public LLMs** — User LLM configs with encrypted API keys, Ollama model control
- **Bulk Delete** — Delete multiple data items, all data for user, all data in memory

## Key Modules

| Module | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `storage.py` | Storage abstraction (local/GCS/Supabase) |
| `config.py` | Config resolution (env > GCS system config > defaults) |
| `smart_routing.py` | Model routing — single source of truth |
| `auth.py` | Auth helpers (`get_authenticated_user_id`, `get_effective_user_id`) |
| `crypto.py` | Fernet encryption for API keys at rest |
| `webhook_events.py` | Dispatches `data.uploaded` to webhook pipeline |
| `telemetry.py` | OpenTelemetry setup |

## Configuration

### Core

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `STORAGE_BACKEND` | auto-detect | `local`, `gcs`, or `supabase` |
| `API_KEY` | (empty) | Global API auth key |
| `MASTER_ENCRYPTION_KEY` | (empty) | Fernet key for encrypting credentials |
| `DEFAULT_USER_ID` | `00000000-...0001` | Default user |

### AI / Model Servers

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `SYSTEM_GEMINI_API_KEY` | — | Gemini key (chat fallback + embeddings) |
| `MODEL_SERVER_URL` | — | Local Ollama (chat primary) |
| `CHAT_COMPLETION_TIMEOUT_S` | `15` | Local Ollama timeout before Gemini fallback |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_API_KEY` | — | Ollama Cloud API key |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_SMALL` | `ollama/gemma3:4b` | Smart routing small tier |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_MEDIUM` | `ollama/gemma3:12b` | Smart routing medium tier |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_LARGE` | `ollama/gemma3:27b` | Smart routing large tier |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_MULTIMODAL` | `ollama/qwen3-vl:235b-cloud` | Vision tier |
| `OLLAMA_CLOUD_MODEL_OMNI` | `ollama/qwen3.5:cloud` | Audio/video tier |
| `DATA_PIPELINE_AI_FALLBACK_MODEL` | `gemini/gemini-3.1-pro-preview` | Fallback for all types |

### Storage

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | Supabase project URL |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Supabase auth key |
| `RAW_BUCKET` | GCS bucket for raw binary files |

### Webhook

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `WEBHOOK_GATEWAY_URL` | Webhook pipeline gateway URL |
| `WEBHOOK_API_KEY` | Webhook gateway auth key |
